      {
        "type": "config",
        "directions": "Select each card to review topics covered in this module."
      },
      {
        "type": "flipCard",
        "cards": [
          {
            "height": "495px",
            "width": "250px",
            "front": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "<strong>Texture</strong>"
              },
              {
                "type": "image",
                "id": "flipimg_01",
                "width": "100%",
                "alt": "a female artist working on a head sculpture",
                "src": "interactives/flipcard_07_04_01/intmedia/p1_img1.jpg"
              }
            ],
            "back": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Texture is an element of art that artists use in both two-dimensional and three-dimensional artwork. Artists carefully choose between actual texture, texture that can be felt in real life, or implied texture, texture that you can see but cannot feel. Artists often use both in mixed media."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "height": "495px",
            "width": "250px",
            "front": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "<strong>Variety and Unity</strong>"
              },
              {
                "type": "image",
                "id": "flipimg_02",
                "width": "100%",
                "alt": "a colorful graphic painting of two head profiles",
                "src": "interactives/flipcard_07_04_01/intmedia/p1_img2.jpg"
              }
            ],
            "back": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Artists use variety and unity to help create a complete work of art that is pleasing to look at and maintains interest."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "height": "495px",
            "width": "250px",
            "front": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "<strong>Mixed Media</strong>"
              },
              {
                "type": "image",
                "id": "flipimg_03",
                "width": "100%",
                "alt": "an illustration of various art supplies",
                "src": "interactives/flipcard_07_04_01/intmedia/p1_img3.jpg"
              }
            ],
            "back": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Mixed media combines various materials and art techniques used in a single work of art. An artist uses mixed media when they use more than one medium."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "type": "flipCard",
        "cards": [
          {
            "height": "495px",
            "width": "250px",
            "front": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "<strong>Assemblage</strong>"
              },
              {
                "type": "image",
                "id": "flipimg_04",
                "width": "100%",
                "alt": "mixed media art with a paper doll holding balloon globes",
                "src": "interactives/flipcard_07_04_01/intmedia/p1_img4.jpg"
              }
            ],
            "back": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Assemblage is an art form in which artists create artwork by assembling found objects or unrelated materials into works of art. The artist will assemble bits and pieces together to make three-dimensional art."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "height": "495px",
            "width": "250px",
            "front": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "<strong>Repurpose</strong>"
              },
              {
                "type": "image",
                "id": "flipimg_05",
                "width": "100%",
                "alt": "a fish mosaic made from plastic bottle caps",
                "src": "interactives/flipcard_07_04_01/intmedia/p1_img5.jpg"
              }
            ],
            "back": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Repurposed materials are given a new life when used for art. Anyone can make art with items from around the house. Artworks created using these materials often look even more superb than initially planned when you use your creative skills!"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "height": "495px",
            "width": "250px",
            "front": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "<strong>El Anatsui</strong>"
              },
              {
                "type": "image",
                "id": "flipimg_06",
                "width": "100%",
                "alt": "an illustration of El Anatsui",
                "src": "interactives/flipcard_07_04_01/intmedia/p1_img6_flvs.png"
              }
            ],
            "back": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "El Anatsui is a renowned artist known for his sculptures and art crafted from recycled and repurposed materials, like bottle caps and metal. His artwork is themed around culture, the environment, and history."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
